        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mens Rea Reform Act of 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill establishes a default &lt;em&gt;mens rea&lt;/em&gt; standard (i.e., state of mind requirement) for federal criminal offenses—statutory and regulatory—that lack an explicit standard.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The government must generally prove that a defendant acted knowingly with respect to each element of an offense for which the text does not specify a state of mind.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
